Set Up and Create a Git Repository

==>download Git from the official site for your operating system.

==> configure git in system


Generating files and initializing the .git directory.
●Create a folder on your desktop and open it.
●Create the files: hello.js, index.html, and helloWorld.java.
●Open the Git terminal and navigate to the folder you have created.
●Execute the following command to initialize the .git repository:
git init


Executing the basic commands.
●Add all the files to your git repository using the following command:
git add	
●Commit the changes using the following command:
git commit -m



Basic commands to setup git as follows:

open git

Become a root user:

# sudo su -

Create a working directory[folder]

# mkdir myproject

Go to inside the directory

# cd myproject

create empty files

# touch hello.js index.html helloWorld.java

======================================
Create a local repo

# git init

=======================================
git configurations:

git config --global user.name sharath


git config --global user.email sk@gmail.com


===================================================

Adding a file to Local repo


# git add .

OR

# git add -a  // add all the files

# git status

# git commit -m "added files"



